13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
15 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
16 This act shall be known and may be cited as the "Oklahoma Space
17 Renaissance Act".
18 SECTION 2. There is hereby appropriated to the Oklahoma Space
19 Industry Development Authority from any monies not otherwise
20 appropriated from the General Revenue Fund of the State Treasury for
21 the fiscal year ending June 30, 2026, the sum of One Million Three
22 Hundred Thousand Dollars ($1,300,000.00) or so much thereof as may
23 be necessary to perform the duties imposed upon the Oklahoma Space
24 Industry Development Authority by law.
ENGR. H. B. NO. 2024 Page 1

1 SECTION 3. There is hereby appropriated to the Oklahoma Space
2 Industry Development Authority from any monies not otherwise
3 appropriated from the General Revenue Fund of the State Treasury for
4 the fiscal year ending June 30, 2026, the sum of Thirty-five Million
5 Dollars ($35,000,000.00) or so much thereof as may be necessary to
6 accomplish infrastructure investments at the Oklahoma Air and Space
7 Port to support testing and launching of spacecraft and for science,
8 technology, engineering, and math (STEM) engagement activities.
9 SECTION 4. There is hereby appropriated to the Oklahoma Space
10 Industry Development Authority from any monies not otherwise
11 appropriated from the General Revenue Fund of the State Treasury for
12 the fiscal year ending June 30, 2026, the sum of Fifteen Million
13 Dollars ($15,000,000.00) or so much thereof as may be necessary to
14 accomplish infrastructure and programmatic investments in a
15 microgravity research consortium focused on applied science for
16 commercialization activities at the Oklahoma City Innovation
17 District in partnership with Oklahoma-based independent research
18 institutes.
19 SECTION 5. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
20 SECTION 6. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
21 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
22 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
23 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
